# Pinia Store Convention

Stores should be created using `defineStore` and expose state, getters and actions. Example from `app.store.ts`:
```typescript
export const useAppStore = defineStore({
  id: "app",
  state: () => ({
    isDark: false,
    language: "en",
  }),
  actions: {
    updateTheme() {
      this.isDark = !this.isDark
      this.isDark ? document.documentElement.classList.add("dark") : document.documentElement.classList.remove("dark")
    },
  },
})

if (import.meta.hot) import.meta.hot.accept(acceptHMRUpdate(useAppStore, import.meta.hot))
```
Keep actions focused and ensure stores remain single responsibility.